@NODE What_is_itc " What is M-Batch?"

M-Batch is a tagged file list manager for DLG.  M-Batch allows users to
delete tagged files from their list by using numbers.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Setting_upc " Setting up M-Batch"

To set up M-Batch, simply add a menu item to the files menu using Overlay and
all other defaults.  Set to executable and call M-Batch thus:

       DLGConfig:Master/M-Batch [-K]

The -K parameter will kill the batch list without displaying it first (Use as
a replacement for the DLG supplied Z command).

Copy the help file into the appropriate menu directory.  Installation is now
complete.

@ENDNODE

@NODE CPS " How CPS rates are calculated."

Characters per second rates are calculated differently for low speed and high
speed modems.  For low speed modems this calculation is used:

   cps = baud x 0.095  ==> 2400 x 0.095 = 228 cps

for high speed modems:

   cps = baud x 0.109  ==> 9600 x 0.109 = 1046 cps

@ENDNODE

@NODE Historyc " History of M-Batch"

Version 1.0  - Initial release.

Version 1.1  - Added remove all option.
             - Changed prompt line to accomodate new option.

Version 1.2  - Fixed a problem when only one file in list.
             - Fixed an error logging problem.

Version 2.0  - Added .CDL support.
             - Removed %PORT parameter.
             - Added -K parameter.

Version 2.0c - Fixed a severe bug when more than 255 files tagged.
             - Now runs M-Support before killing the tagged list.

Version 2.1  - If registered, only displays the program ID on most occasions.
               The 'registered to' banner will appear randomly upon exit.

Version 2.2  - Now accepts comma as seperator when inputing file numbers.

Version 3.0  - A few minor optimisations.


@ENDNODE

